# PR descriptions use HTML

When creating or updating a GitHub pull request body, write the description in **HTML**, not Markdown.

## Required shape

```html
<h2>Summary</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Player-facing change in plain language</li>
  <li>Version bump if applicable (e.g. → <strong>1.1.0</strong>)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Test plan</h2>
<ul>
  <li>[ ] Concrete check someone can perform</li>
</ul>
```

## Rules

- Use `<h2>`, `<ul>`, `<li>`, `<p>`, `<strong>`, `<code>` as needed
- Do **not** use Markdown headings (`##`), bullets (`-`), or `**bold**`
- Keep the repo PR template (`.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`) in sync with this format
- Fine to leave a short plain “Made with Cursor” line after the HTML if the tooling adds it
